s explored mechanistic differences. Relative to the \$\${\textbackslash}textbackslashhbox \{PV\}\_\{{\textbackslash}textbackslashtext\{HC\}\}\$\$model, the \$\${\textbackslash}textbackslashhbox \{PV\}\_\{{\textbackslash}textbackslashtext\{MS-DBB\}\}\$\$model exhibited higher sensitivity to calcium accumulation, permitting a faster rate of calcium-dependent recovery from STD. In conclusion, resistance of \$\${\textbackslash}textbackslashhbox \{PV\}\_\{{\textbackslash}textbackslashtext\{MS-DBB\}\}\$\$synapses to STD during short gamma bursts enables robust long-range GABAergic transmission from MS-DBB to hippocampus.},
